Responses\: success - Date/time retrieved successfully. failure - Date/time could not be retrieved. 75c1fa61-5862-43b8-8e28-8e8df7146eda.b57c759b-b477-4f53-a3fc-60e461bbf999.prompt=Password\: 75c1fa61-5862-43b8-8e28-8e8df7146eda.bf8e0299-9854-41b6-8bb8-48e1104c3b87.description=
This operation creates a UNC path given a host and a normal path. This operation does not check the validity of the given path or the existence of the given host. 

Input Parameters\:
host - the host to which the path refers to.
path - a path that will be converted to UNC.

Returns\:
The corresponding UNC path for the given host and path.

Responses\:
failure - the conversion to UNC failed
success - the conversion to UNC succeeded.
75c1fa61-5862-43b8-8e28-8e8df7146eda.description=
Delete files with specified extension in a remote machine, with an optional date input.

Inputs \:
host		- Host from where the file will be removed.
user		- User credentials of the system in which the delete operation has to be performed.
password		- Password of the user login.
directory		- Path of the folder in which the delete operation has to be performed.
extension		- Extension of the files that have to be deleted.
time		- The date before which the files have to be deleted. (optional, required in format MM-dd-yyyy HH\:mm).

Responses \:
success		- Delete operation performed successfully.
failure		- Error occurred while executing  the flow.
75c1fa61-5862-43b8-8e28-8e8df7146eda.e3878ce8-c917-4b00-9aa9-88ead53fcf74.prompt=Enter the path\: 75c1fa61-5862-43b8-8e28-8e8df7146eda.e4620adc-ffa3-42ec-9fee-68948710321d.description=
If the input dateFormat is not specified, it converts a date in the format of date/time of OO Central Server's, which is dependant on the Java locale, to a date either in the format of date/time of OO Central Server's or in the format specified in the input outFormat. 

If the input dateFormat is specified, it converts a date in the format in dateFormat to a date either in the format of date/time of OO Central Server's or in the format specified in the input outFormat.

You can use flow "Get Current Date and Time" to check upon the default date/time format.  

For exmaple, if OO Central Server's locale is English, the input dateFormat is empty and the input outFormat is empty, the input date should be in the format of "July 13, 2006 10\:04\:08 AM". If the user specifies dateFormat as "dd-MM-YYYY HH\:mm\:ss", the input date should be in the format of "13-07-2006 10\:04\:08". If the input outFormat is empty, the result will be "July 13, 2006 10\:04\:08 AM". If the input outFormat is "yyyy-MM-dd", the result will be "2006-07-13".


Specify the date format with the following patterns\:

Letter 	Date or Time Component 	Presentation 	Examples
G 	Era designator 	Text 	AD
y 	Year 	Year 	1996; 96
M 	Month in year 	Month 	July; Jul; 07
w 	Week in year 	Number 	27
W 	Week in month 	Number 	2
D 	Day in year 	Number 	189
d 	Day in month 	Number 	10
F 	Day of week in month 	Number 	2
E 	Day in week 	Text 	Tuesday; Tue
a 	Am/pm marker 	Text 	PM
H 	Hour in day (0-23) 	Number 	0
k 	Hour in day (1-24) 	Number 	24
K 	Hour in am/pm (0-11) 	Number 	0
h 	Hour in am/pm (1-12) 	Number 	12
m 	Minute in hour 	Number 	30
s 	Second in minute 	Number 	55
S 	Millisecond 	Number 	978
z 	Time zone 	General time zone 	Pacific Standard Time; PST; GMT-08\:00
Z 	Time zone 	RFC 822 time zone 	-0800

So, for example\: the date "2006-07-10 15\:16\:14.766 PDT" would have the dateFormat "yyyy-MM-dd HH\:mm\:ss.SSS z".

You can also use single quotes (') to avoid text interpretation. The quoted text will simply be copied into the output string during formatting (if present in the outFormat) or matched against the input string during parsing (if present in the dateFormat). For example, the date value "2006-07-10T15\:16\:14.766Z" would have the dateFormat "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH\:mm\:ss.SSS'Z'". 


Inputs\:
date - The date to parse. If the input dateFormat is empty, the date must be in the format of date/time of OO Central Server's, which is dependant on the Java locale. If the input dateFormat is not empty, the date must be in the format specified in the input dateFormat.
dateFormat - The format of the input date. 
outFormat - The format of the output date/time. If it is empty, the output date/time will be in the format of date/time of OO Cental Server's, which is dependant on the Java locale.
outLocaleLang - The locale language for output string. For example,  en or ja.
outLocaleCountry - The locale country for output string. For example, US or JP. 

Responses\:
success - The date was converted.
failure - The date could not be converted.

Result\:
The date in the new format.
75c1fa61-5862-43b8-8e28-8e8df7146eda.e8c8474e-fd08-4a0f-a6e5-9f354aba8677.prompt=Date (MM-dd-yyyy HH\:mm) \: 75c1fa61-5862-43b8-8e28-8e8df7146eda.f06a0358-a0bb-45eb-b240-143b1a76e155.prompt=Remote host where the delete operation is executed\: 75c1fa61-5862-43b8-8e28-8e8df7146eda.f122a833-740c-4b99-8b9c-c710788183a9.description=Compares two dates. The inputs must be in the format of date/time format of OO Central Server's, which is dependant of Java Locale. You can use flow " Get Current Date and Time" to check upon the default date/time format. For exmaple, If OO Central Server's locale is English, the input date should be in the format of "July 13, 2006 10\:04\:08 AM". Inputs\: d1 - The first date. For example, if the locale is English, the format should be "July 12, 2006 4\:23\:20 PM" d2 - The second date. For example, if the locale is English, the format should be "July 12, 2006 4\:23\:20 PM" threshold -The number of milliseconds around each date that still allows the dates to be considered equal. Responses\: before - if d1 is before d2. equal - if d1 is < d2 + threshold and d1 > d2-threshold. after - if d1 is after d2. failure - Something went wrong. Returns\: the value of d1-d2 in milliseconds. 75c1fa61-5862-43b8-8e28-8e8df7146eda.f1891f55-a475-4d55-b1ab-96a7f6ebfa4c.prompt=Drectory in which to delete \: 75c1fa61-5862-43b8-8e28-8e8df7146eda.f2d3876e-319d-4604-9aea-674cd83ee596.prompt=File extension (eg. txt, xls, etc.) \: 75c1fa61-5862-43b8-8e28-8e8df7146eda.f5699901-e159-4a09-9795-97de03e59972.prompt=Enter the Directory in which to Delete \: 75c1fa61-5862-43b8-8e28-8e8df7146eda.fbad2726-5111-4a0e-9fbc-4faf11089644.description=
To Delete files with specified extension in local machine with an optional date input.

Inputs \:
directory		- Path of the folder in which the delete operation has to be performed.
extension		- Extension of the files that have to be deleted.
time		- The date before which the files have to be deleted. (this input is an optional one).
user		- User credentials of the system in which the delete operation has to be performed.
password		- Password of the particular user in the system in which the delete operation has to be performed.

Responses \:
success		- if the desired delete operation performed successfully.
failure		- any error occurs while executing  the flow.
